question: What kind of allergy has the code 84489001?
answers:
```sql
SELECT
  d.DESCRIPTION
FROM allergies AS a
LEFT JOIN patients AS p
  ON a.PATIENT = p.ID
LEFT JOIN encounters AS e
  ON a.ENCOUNTER = e.ID
LEFT JOIN organizations AS o
  ON e.ORGANIZATION = o.ID
LEFT JOIN providers AS pr
  ON e.PROVIDER = pr.ID
LEFT JOIN payers AS pa
  ON e.PAYER = pa.ID
LEFT JOIN conditions AS d
  ON a.CODE = d.CODE
WHERE
  a.CODE = 84489001;
```

question: Which illness is most common in warmer climates?
answers:
```sql
SELECT
  d.DESCRIPTION,
  COUNT(*) AS count_encounters
FROM encounters AS e
JOIN ORGANIZATIONS AS o
  ON e.ORGANIZATION = o.Id
JOIN patients AS p
  ON e.PATIENT = p.Id
JOIN conditions AS d
  ON e.PATIENT = d.PATIENT AND e.ENCOUNTER = d.ENCOUNTER
WHERE
  o.CITY IN (
    SELECT
      CITY
    FROM ORGANIZATIONS
    WHERE
      LAT > 30
  )
GROUP BY
  d.DESCRIPTION
ORDER BY
  count_encounters DESC
LIMIT 1;
```

question: Please provide me reasons for performing the procedure Auscultation of the fetal heart.
answers:
```sql
SELECT
  pt.first,
  pt.last,
  m.name,
  GROUP_CONCAT( DISTINCT c.reasondescription || ' || ' || c.reasoncode ) AS reasons
FROM patients AS pt
JOIN encounters AS e
  ON pt.id = e.patient
JOIN procedures AS p
  ON e.id = p.encounter
JOIN payers AS m
  ON e.payer = m.id
JOIN medications AS c
  ON p.patient = c.patient
  AND p.encounter = c.encounter
  AND p.code = c.code
WHERE
  p.description = 'Auscultation of the fetal heart'
GROUP BY
  pt.id,
  pt.first,
  pt.last,
  m.name
ORDER BY
  reasons DESC;
```

question: What is the successrate of medication 24 HR Metformin hydrochloride 500 MG Extended Release Oral Tablet?
answers:
```sql
SELECT
  p.FIRST AS Firstname,
  p.LAST AS Lastname,
  m.DESCRIPTION AS Medication_Name,
  AVG(CASE WHEN m.TYPE = 'Dispense' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Success_Rate, /* Average should be for the desired type */
  SUM(CASE WHEN m.TYPE = 'Dispense' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Total_Dispenses /* Sum should be for the desired type */
FROM Medications AS m
LEFT JOIN Patients AS p
  ON p.ID = m.PATIENT
LEFT JOIN Payers AS payer
  ON payer.ID = m.PAYER
LEFT JOIN Encounters AS e
  ON e.ID = m.ENCOUNTER
WHERE
  m.CODE = '24 HR Metformin hydrochloride 500 MG Extended Release Oral Tablet'
GROUP BY
  p.FIRST,
  p.LAST,
  m.DESCRIPTION;
```

question: Please provide me the name of the patients related to the device Blood glucose meter (physical object).
answers:
```sql
WITH CountEncounters AS (
  SELECT
    p.first,
    p.last,
    COUNT(DISTINCT e.id)
  FROM patients
  p
  LEFT JOIN devices
    d ON p.id = d.patient
  LEFT JOIN encounters
    e ON p.id = e.patient
  WHERE
    d.description = 'Blood glucose meter (physical object)'
  GROUP BY
    p.first,
    p.last
)
SELECT
  first,
  last,
  COUNT(DISTINCT id) AS encounter_count
FROM CountEncounters
GROUP BY
  first,
  last
ORDER BY
  encounter_count DESC;
```

question: What is the most promising procedure for a patient with Mold (organism)?
answers:
```sql
/* Most Promising Procedure for a Patient with Mold (organism) */
SELECT
  p.first,
  p.last,
  m.description AS mold_description,
  pro.description AS procedure_description,
  CASE WHEN pro.code = '12345' THEN 'High' WHEN pro.code = '23456' THEN 'Medium' ELSE 'Low' END AS procedure_promising_level
FROM patients AS p
JOIN encounters AS e
  ON p.id = e.patient
JOIN allergies AS al
  ON e.id = al.encounter
JOIN conditions AS c
  ON e.id = c.encounter
JOIN medications AS m
  ON e.id = m.encounter
JOIN procedures AS pro
  ON e.id = pro.encounter
WHERE
  c.description LIKE 'Mold'
ORDER BY
  procedure_promising_level DESC;
```

question: Please provide me the encounters that were related to the procedure with code 171207006.
answers:
```sql
SELECT
  DISTINCT
  e.id AS encounter_id,
  e.description AS encounter_description,
  e.code AS encounter_code,
  e.start AS encounter_start,
  e.stop AS encounter_stop,
  e.reasoncode AS encounter_reasoncode,
  e.reasonDescription AS encounter_reason_description,
  p.id AS patient_id,
  p.first AS patient_first_name,
  p.last AS patient_last_name,
  po.name AS organization_name,
  pr.name AS provider_name,
  pay.name AS payer_name
FROM encounters AS e
JOIN procedures AS pro
  ON e.id = pro.encounter
JOIN patients AS p
  ON pro.patient = p.id
LEFT JOIN payers AS pay
  ON e.payer = pay.id
LEFT JOIN providers AS pr
  ON e.provider = pr.id
LEFT JOIN organizations AS po
  ON e.organization = po.id
WHERE
  pro.code = 171207006;
```

question: What is the average quality of life score for customers under the payer name Blue Cross Blue Shield?

SELECT
  p.name,
  q.qols_avg
FROM payers AS p
JOIN patients AS pat
  ON p.id = pat.payer
JOIN encounters AS e
  ON pat.id = e.patient
JOIN payer_transitions AS pt
  ON pat.id = pt.patient
JOIN qols AS q
  ON p.id = q.payer
WHERE
  q.qols_avg = (

    FROM qols AS q
  );
```

question: Please provide me the number of procedures uncovered by the payer Anthem.

  ON e.payer = py.id
WHERE
  py.name = 'Anthem' AND p.code NOT IN (
    SELECT
      p.code
    FROM procedures AS p
    LEFT JOIN encounters AS e
      ON p.encounter = e.id
    LEFT JOIN patients AS pt

    LEFT JOIN payers AS py
      ON e.payer = py.id

      py.name = 'Anthem'

```

question: What is the most promising procedure for a patient with Allergy to substance (finding)?
answers:
```sql
SELECT
  p.first,
  p.last,
  pro.description,
  COUNT(pro.patient)
FROM procedures AS pro
LEFT JOIN encounters AS enc
  ON pro.encounter = enc.id
LEFT JOIN patients AS p
  ON pro.patient = p.id
WHERE
  enc.id IN (
    SELECT
      enc.id
    FROM allergies AS al
    LEFT JOIN encounters AS enc
      ON al.encounter = enc.id
    WHERE
      al.code IN (
        SELECT
          code
        FROM allergies
        WHERE
          description = 'Allergy to substance (finding)'
      )
  )
GROUP BY
  pro.description
ORDER BY
  COUNT(pro.patient) DESC
LIMIT 1;
```

question: What are the survival chances of allgery Aspirin?
answers:
```sql
SELECT
  a.description AS allergy_name,
  count(c.start) AS total_cases,
  SUM(CASE WHEN c.stop IS NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS alive_cases,
  (
    SUM(CASE WHEN c.stop IS NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100 / count(c.start)
  ) AS survival_rate
FROM allergies AS a
JOIN conditions AS c
  ON a.code = c.code
GROUP BY
  a.description
ORDER BY
  survival_rate DESC;
```

question: What is the successrate of medication 72 HR Fentanyl 0.025 MG/HR Transdermal System?
answers:
```sql
SELECT
  medications.code,
  COUNT(DISTINCT medications.id) AS total_prescriptions,
  COUNT(DISTINCT claims.id) AS total_claims,
  (
    COUNT(DISTINCT medications.id) / COUNT(DISTINCT claims.id)
  ) AS success_rate /* Calculate success rate as total prescriptions divided by total claims */
FROM medications
JOIN encounters
  ON medications.encounter = encounters.id
JOIN patients
  ON encounters.patient = patients.id
LEFT JOIN claims
  ON claims.patientid = patients.id
WHERE
  medications.code = '72'
GROUP BY
  medications.code;
```

question: Please provide me the number of immunizations uncovered by the payer Cigna Health.
answers:
```sql
SELECT
  COUNT(DISTINCT i.id)
FROM immunizations AS i
JOIN encounters AS e
  ON i.ENCOUNTER = e.ID
JOIN patients AS p
  ON e.PATIENT = p.ID
JOIN payers AS py
  ON e.PAYER = py.ID
JOIN medications AS m
  ON i.PATIENT = m.PATIENT AND i.ENCOUNTER = m.ENCOUNTER
WHERE
  py.NAME = 'Cigna Health' AND i.CODE = m.CODE AND m.PAYER_COVERAGE = 0;
```

question: How long does Hydrochlorothiazide 25 MG Oral Tablet effect last?
answers:
```sql
SELECT
  m.description,
  m.stop - m.start AS days
FROM medications AS m
WHERE
  m.code IN ('402543', '502125')
GROUP BY
  m.description
ORDER BY
  days DESC;
```
